\section{Disk I/O routines}

@ The EALDR RWTS (Read/Write Track/Sector) occupies [[$BC00]]--[[$BFFF]]
and provides the disk routines used by the EALDR~VM to load game data.
These routines are structurally identical to the [[BOOT1]] disk routines
at [[$0900]]--[[$0CFF]] (see~\S\ref{sec:boot1}), relocated to different
addresses and using different zero-page locations:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{lll}
\toprule
\thead{Purpose} & \thead{BOOT1} & \thead{EALDR RWTS} \\
\midrule
Scratch variables      & [[$26]]/[[$27]] & [[$4A]]/[[$4B]] \\
Address header fields  & [[$2C]]--[[$2F]] & [[$38]]--[[$3B]] \\
Slot index             & [[$2B]] (variable) & [[$60]] (hardcoded) \\
Current track          & [[$09C6]]  & [[$BC0C]] \\
Error flag             & [[$09C7]]  & [[$BC0D]] \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

Four entry points at [[$BC00]] are JMP trampolines used by the EALDR~VM:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{lll}
\toprule
\thead{Entry} & \thead{Target} & \thead{Function} \\
\midrule
[[$BC00]] & [[$BCD4]] & Move disk arm to half-track in~[[A]] \\
[[$BC03]] & [[$BF00]] & Read one track (16 sectors) to memory at page~[[$3E]] \\
[[$BC06]] & [[$BD21]] & Search for next address field \\
[[$BC09]] & [[$BD14]] & Delay (enters [[EALDR_RWTS_DELAY]] inner loop) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The sector loader at [[$BF1F]] builds a destination page table from the
interleave table at [[$BF64]] and reads all~16 sectors using
[[EALDR_RWTS_SEARCH_ADDR]] and [[EALDR_RWTS_READ_SECTOR]].

<<EALDR disk entry points>>=
    ORG     $BC00
EALDR_MOVE_ARM_TRAMPOLINE:
    JMP     EALDR_RWTS_MOVE_ARM
EALDR_READ_TRACK_TRAMPOLINE:               ; $BC03
    JMP     EALDR_RWTS_READ_TRACK
EALDR_SEARCH_ADDR_TRAMPOLINE:              ; $BC06
    JMP     EALDR_RWTS_SEARCH_ADDR
EALDR_READ_DATA_TRAMPOLINE:                ; $BC09
    JMP     EALDR_RWTS_DELAY_INNER
@ %def EALDR_MOVE_ARM_TRAMPOLINE EALDR_READ_TRACK_TRAMPOLINE EALDR_SEARCH_ADDR_TRAMPOLINE EALDR_READ_DATA_TRAMPOLINE

@ [[EALDR_RWTS_TRACK]] at [[$BC0C]] holds the current track number
(modified by [[EALDR_RWTS_MOVE_ARM]]).  [[EALDR_RWTS_ERROR_FLAG]] at
[[$BC0D]] is set by [[EALDR_RWTS_READ_TRACK]] when a timeout occurs.
[[EALDR_RWTS_READ_ERROR]] at [[$BC0E]] is the error-return entry point:
it sets carry and returns.

<<EALDR RWTS track vars>>=
    ORG     $BC0C
EALDR_RWTS_TRACK:
    HEX     00              ; current track number
EALDR_RWTS_ERROR_FLAG:
    HEX     00              ; nonzero = error occurred
EALDR_RWTS_READ_ERROR:
    SEC
    RTS
@ %def EALDR_RWTS_TRACK EALDR_RWTS_ERROR_FLAG EALDR_RWTS_READ_ERROR


