INIT_STUB:
    RTS
@ %def INIT_STUB
Called once from [[GAME_INIT]] to set up the game display and run the
opening tune.  Steps:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Calls [[$5C6D]] to initialize the game display (draws borders,
  sets text windows).
\item Sets [[DISPATCH_VEC]] to point to the game action handler at [[$5B2A]],
  used by the tune player's indirect dispatch at [[$7A49]].
\item Clears [[$5A00]] (game state flag).
\item Patches [[$80A6]] to [[$B1]] ([[LDA (zp),Y]] opcode), restoring
  the character renderer's indirect load.
\item Runs the opening tune (index~6) via [[TUNE_PLAYER]].
\item Patches [[$7A49--$7A4B]] from [[JMP (DISPATCH_VEC)]] to [[JMP $7A4F]],
  disabling the indirect action handler now that init is complete.
\end{enumerate}

@ [[INIT_GAME_STATE]] stores [[GAME_ACTION_HANDLER]] into the zero-page
vector [[DISPATCH_VEC]] ([[$F6/$F7]]).  The tune player uses this vector
for indirect action dispatch; after the opening tune finishes,
[[INIT_GAME_STATE]] patches the dispatch site to bypass the vector entirely.

