We run into an issue when we look at the song table for the splash screen. The
very first note played is low [[3F]]. This is closest to [[G5]], although it
results in a frequency of [[771.9]] Hz, which is less accurate than the [[783.7]] Hz
that would be given by [[3F]]. In fact, all the low tones are off by a bit,
unless we assume that the programmer erred, thinking that the low tones were
just one octave below the high tones. In that case, we should just use the high
tone table and subtract one octave for the low tones.

@ The splash song bytecode is documented in [[TUNE_3_ATTRACT]]
(\S\ref{sec:tune_player}).

@ [[NUM_TO_DECIMAL]] writes five digit positions starting from
[[DECIMAL_OUT_PTR]] (ten-thousands, thousands, hundreds, tens, ones).
Leading zeros are suppressed (the pre-cleared spaces remain).  These
EQUs mark where each stat's ten-thousands position falls in the
template, so that the rightmost digits land on the placeholder ``00''s.

<<defines>>=
STATS_LIFE_OUT      EQU     STATS_LIFE-3     ; $7D8D: life force output (2 digits at +3,+4)
STATS_STR_OUT       EQU     STATS_STR-3      ; $7D9C: strength output
STATS_DUCATS_OUT    EQU     STATS_DUCATS-1   ; $7DB6: ducats/experience output (5 digits at +0..+4)
STATS_SPEED_OUT     EQU     STATS_SPEED-3    ; $7DC6: speed output
STATS_SWORD_OUT     EQU     STATS_SWORD-3    ; $7DD2: sword output
STATS_WEAP_OUT      EQU     STATS_WEAP       ; $7DE1: weapons/group count output
STATS_DEXT_OUT      EQU     STATS_DEXT-3     ; $7DF0: dexterity output
STATS_DAGGR_OUT     EQU     STATS_DAGGR-3    ; $7DFC: dagger output
@ %def STATS_LIFE_OUT STATS_STR_OUT STATS_DUCATS_OUT STATS_SPEED_OUT STATS_SWORD_OUT STATS_WEAP_OUT STATS_DEXT_OUT STATS_DAGGR_OUT

@ \subsection{Game configuration and menu strings (\$7AAC--\$7D82)}

The region \$7AAC--\$7D82 contains game configuration variables and
the complete set of menu option display strings.

\paragraph{Configuration variables (\$7AAC--\$7ADB).}
Includes blink delay ([[BLINK_DELAY]]), animation frame tables
([[ANIM_WAIT_TABLE]], [[ANIM_FRAME_TABLE]]), map tile defaults
([[TILE_DEFAULT_TAB]], [[TILE_FILL_TAB]], [[TILE_BLINK_TAB]]),
save/load parameters ([[SLOT_NUMBER]], [[GAME_DISK_SLOTS]],
[[SAVE_TRACK_BASE]], [[DISK_SIGNATURE]]), and other runtime state
--- all documented via EQU labels elsewhere.

\paragraph{Menu strings (\$7ADC--\$7D82).}
Length-prefixed high-ASCII strings for all menu options: action menus
(MOVE, ATTACK, REST, DEFEND), combat (direction labels, target names),
shop (PAY/BUY/NO SALE), settings (SOUND, SPEED, DANGER), character
management (ADD SOMEONE, RETIRE, DROP GOLD/ARMOR), save/load
(CONTINUE GAME, BEGIN NEW GAME, scenario disk options), and treasure
chest messages.  Several strings contain mutable fields: digit
placeholders in ``CONTINUE GAME NUMBER NN'' ([[S_CONTINUE_TENS]]/
[[S_CONTINUE_ONES]]), ``SAVE GAME IN SLOT NUMBER 00'', and
``PAY 000000 FOR'' (price display), plus the 20-byte name buffer
at [[ATTACK_NAME_BUF]] and drop amount display at
[[DROP_DISPLAY_BUF]].

