@ \subsection{Runtime data area (\$A8F2--\$B2FF)}

The region \$A8F2--\$B2FF is a 2,574-byte runtime data area,
initialized to mostly zeros in the disk image.  The first 14~bytes
(\$A8F2--\$A8FF) contain non-zero initialization data; the remaining
2,560~bytes (\$A900--\$B2FF) are zeroed.  During gameplay, this area
is used extensively as working storage with 77~absolute-addressed
references from across the program, including:
\begin{itemize}
\item Entity/mob runtime state (\$A919, \$A960, \$A964, \$A96C, \$A974)
\item Subroutine at \$AB45 (called from game data at \$4A64)
\item Display buffer at \$B120 (indexed load from \$1980)
\item Comparison data at \$ABD0 (tested from \$59FE, \$5A65, \$5AE3)
\item Disk I/O state (\$ADBB, \$AFBA)
\item Jump vector at \$AD06 (from \$0601)
\end{itemize}
Full decomposition of individual fields is deferred.

