selected by [[DISPLAY_SHOP]] based on the entity's type byte
(byte~1 of [[ENTITY_REC]], minus~\$D5).  Record~0 is the weapon
shop; record~1 is the armor shop.

Each record contains five 5-byte item slots at offsets \$00, \$05,
\$0A, \$0F, and~\$14.  Each slot holds a 2-byte buy-effect handler
address, a 2-byte item name string pointer, and a 1-byte
price-per-unit value.  The entity's bitmask (byte~2, stored in
[[SHOP_VALID_MASK]]) determines which slots are displayed; unused slots contain
display format data.  Bytes \$19--\$27 hold additional items or
display format strings.  Byte~\$28 is the shop scene number (passed
to [[SCENE_LOOP]] when entering the shop).

\paragraph{Item name strings (\$7F2F--\$7FBD).}
Ten length-prefixed high-ASCII item name strings (5~weapons,
5~armor), interleaved with the [[SHOP_EFFECT_TABLE]] (5~bytes at
\$7F6D) and the [[XP_AWARD_TABLE]] (5~bytes at \$7FBE).
The substring ``CHAIN MAIL'' at \$7FA9 is referenced directly by
6~callers in [[CLASSIFY_ENTITY_TYPE]] (\$1178--\$11ED).

\paragraph{Map object names (\$7FC3--\$8039).}
Eight length-prefixed strings for map tile descriptions:
A WALL, A STATUE, A TREASURE CHEST, EMPTY SPACE, AN ILLUSION,
A DOOR, AN INVISIBLE WALL!, SOME RUNE WRITING, A TRADING OUTPOST.
The string at \$8003 (``AN INVISIBLE WALL!'') is referenced from
the relocated block at \$A3A7.

\paragraph{Attack verb strings (\$803A--\$80A3).}
Fourteen length-prefixed combat verb strings, indexed by damage
level (low to high): JABS, POKES, HITS, CLOUTS, POUNDS, SMACKS,
SMITES, WHOPS, WHACKS, BASHES, WHOMPS, WALLOPS, SMASHES,
CLOBBERS, LAMBASTES.  The table base at \$807D is referenced from
the attack display routine at \$7E2E.

