@ \subsection{Save/load slot routines (\$62EC--\$633F)}

[[SAVE_LOAD_INIT]] is the initialization callback for the save/load menu
([[SAVE_LOAD_TABLE]]).  It calls [[FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER]] to display the
current slot number, then returns.

<<defines>>=
SLOT_NUMBER         EQU     $7AC0   ; current save/load slot number
MAX_SLOT_NUMBER     EQU     $7AC6   ; maximum slot number
S_CONTINUE_TENS     EQU     $7BF1   ; tens digit in "CONTINUE GAME NUMBER NN"
S_CONTINUE_ONES     EQU     $7BF2   ; ones digit in "CONTINUE GAME NUMBER NN"
S_SAVE_SLOT_TENS    EQU     $7D81   ; tens digit in "SAVE GAME IN SLOT NUMBER 00"
S_SAVE_SLOT_ONES    EQU     $7D82   ; ones digit in "SAVE GAME IN SLOT NUMBER 00"
@ %def SLOT_NUMBER MAX_SLOT_NUMBER S_CONTINUE_TENS S_CONTINUE_ONES S_SAVE_SLOT_TENS S_SAVE_SLOT_ONES

<<save load init>>=
    ORG     $62EC
SAVE_LOAD_INIT:
    JSR     FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER ; format current slot number into strings
    RTS
@ %def SAVE_LOAD_INIT

@ [[SLOT_INC]] increments [[SLOT_NUMBER]].  If the result exceeds
[[MAX_SLOT_NUMBER]], it clamps back.  Either way, it patches the menu
record via [[$6071]] and reformats the display.

[[SLOT_DEC]] decrements [[SLOT_NUMBER]].  If it reaches zero, it wraps
back to~1.

[[SLOT_UPDATE]] patches the current menu record via [[$6071]], then
jumps to [[FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER]] to redisplay the number.

[[SLOT_INC_ENTER]] and [[SLOT_DEC_ENTER]] are the menu handlers for the
\# and @ arrow keys in the save/load menu.  They adjust the slot number
and re-enter [[INIT_WORLD]] (which presents the save/load menu).

[[FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER]] converts [[SLOT_NUMBER]] (1--19) into two
high-ASCII decimal digits and writes them into both the ``CONTINUE GAME
NUMBER'' and ``SAVE GAME IN SLOT NUMBER'' display strings.  Values below
10 get a leading space; values 10--19 get a ``1'' tens digit.

<<slot number routines>>=
    ORG     $62F0
SLOT_INC:
    INC     SLOT_NUMBER
    LDA     SLOT_NUMBER
    CMP     MAX_SLOT_NUMBER
    BCC     SLOT_UPDATE        ; still below max -> update display
    DEC     SLOT_NUMBER        ; undo: clamp to max
    JMP     SLOT_UPDATE

SLOT_DEC:
    DEC     SLOT_NUMBER
    BNE     SLOT_UPDATE        ; nonzero -> update display
    INC     SLOT_NUMBER        ; undo: wrap 0 -> 1

SLOT_UPDATE:
    JSR     $6071              ; patch menu record
    JMP     FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER

SLOT_INC_ENTER:
    JSR     SLOT_INC
    JMP     INIT_WORLD

SLOT_DEC_ENTER:
    JSR     SLOT_DEC
    JMP     INIT_WORLD

FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER:
    LDA     #$A0               ; space (high ASCII)
    STA     S_CONTINUE_TENS    ; default tens digit to space
    STA     S_SAVE_SLOT_TENS
    LDA     SLOT_NUMBER
    CMP     #$0A               ; >= 10?
    BCC     .ones              ; no -> skip tens
    SEC
    SBC     #$0A               ; remainder
    PHA
    LDA     #$B1               ; "1" (high ASCII)
    STA     S_CONTINUE_TENS
    STA     S_SAVE_SLOT_TENS
    PLA
.ones:
    ORA     #$B0               ; convert 0-9 to high ASCII digit
    STA     S_CONTINUE_ONES
    STA     S_SAVE_SLOT_ONES
    RTS
@ %def SLOT_INC SLOT_DEC SLOT_UPDATE SLOT_INC_ENTER SLOT_DEC_ENTER FORMAT_SLOT_NUMBER

@ \subsection{Save game slot menu (\$6340--\$637E)}

The save game slot menu is entered from the ``SAVE GAME'' option in the
game settings menu.  It presents four options:
\begin{itemize}
\item MOVE --- return to the game ([[MOVE_LOOP]])
\item SAVE GAME IN SLOT NUMBER NN --- save to the current slot ([[SAVE_GAME]])
\item \# --- increment slot number ([[SLOT_INC_REENTER]])
\item @ --- decrement slot number ([[SLOT_DEC_REENTER]])
