@ \subsection{Character selection menu (\$63A8--\$6457)}

The character selection menu is used when the player is asked to choose
a character---for example, when an NPC offers to join the party (``ADD
SOMEONE'') or when the game needs a specific character selected.  Six
options are available:
\begin{itemize}
\item MOVE --- return to the game ([[MOVE_LOOP]])
\item ADD [name] --- add the currently displayed character ([[INIT_CHAR_SELECT]])
\item \# --- browse to the next PC ([[CHAR_SELECT_NEXT]])
\item @ --- browse to the previous PC ([[CHAR_SELECT_PREV]])
\item TO THIS ROOM --- transport character here ([[CHAR_SELECT_HERE]])
\item TO ALI BABA'S HOME --- send character home ([[CHAR_SELECT_HOME]])
\end{itemize}

Records~4 and~5 are dynamically enabled by [[CHAR_SELECT_INIT]] based on
whether [[CURRENT_PLAYER]] equals~9.  The table's [[max\_range]] is also
patched at runtime.

<<char select table>>=
    ORG     $63A8
CHAR_SELECT_TABLE:
    ; 6 options, max_range=2, init=$626B (patched at runtime)
    DC.B    $06,$02
    DC.W    $626B
    ; rec0: MOVE
    HEX     01 05 06 02 06 02
    DC.W    $7D53              ; "MOVE"
    DC.W    MOVE_LOOP
    ; rec1: ADD [character name]
    HEX     01 2D 01 05 01 03
    DC.W    $7B47              ; "ADD" + CHAR_SELECT_NAME buffer
    DC.W    INIT_CHAR_SELECT   ; add character handler
    ; rec2: # (next PC)
    HEX     01 49 01 05 02 04
    DC.W    $7B60              ; "#"
    DC.W    CHAR_SELECT_NEXT
    ; rec3: @ (previous PC)
    HEX     01 4B 01 05 03 05
    DC.W    $7B62              ; "@"
    DC.W    CHAR_SELECT_PREV
    ; rec4: TO THIS ROOM (dynamically enabled)
    HEX     01 55 02 06 04 06
    DC.W    $7B27              ; "TO THIS ROOM"
    DC.W    CHAR_SELECT_HERE
    ; rec5: TO ALI BABA'S HOME (dynamically enabled)
    HEX     00 55 05 01 05 01
    DC.W    $7B34              ; "TO ALI BABA'S HOME"
    DC.W    CHAR_SELECT_HOME
@ %def CHAR_SELECT_TABLE

@ [[ENTER_CHAR_SELECT]] loads the character selection table and enters
[[INPUT_LOOP]].  This is the jump target from [[INIT_CHAR_SELECT]] at
\$0B4F.

[[CHAR_SELECT_INIT]] is called when the ``Add Someone'' option is
selected from the ``Other Options'' menu.  It calls [[FIND_FIRST_PC]]
to locate a player character.  If none found (carry set), it displays
message~\$35 (``YOU SAVED ME FROM MY IMPRISONMENT,'') and returns to
[[MOVE_LOOP]].

If a PC is found, it checks [[CURRENT_PLAYER]].  If equal to~9, records~4
and~5 (TO THIS ROOM / TO ALI BABA'S HOME) are both enabled, and
[[ACTIVE_CHAR]] is set to~1.  Otherwise, record~4 is enabled (with
[[CURRENT_PLAYER]] stored in [[ACTIVE_CHAR]]), record~5 is disabled,
and the table's [[max\_range]] is set to~2.  Control then jumps to
[[ENTER_CHAR_SELECT]].

[[CHAR_SELECT_NEXT]] and [[CHAR_SELECT_PREV]] browse through player
characters.  They patch the current menu record via [[$6071]], advance
or retreat in the PC list, then re-enter the character selection menu.

[[CHAR_SELECT_HERE]] and [[CHAR_SELECT_HOME]] are the handlers for
the ``TO THIS ROOM'' and ``TO ALI BABA'S HOME'' options.  They patch
the table's enable flags based on [[CURRENT_PLAYER]] and re-enter the
menu.

<<char select handlers>>=
    ORG     $63E8
ENTER_CHAR_SELECT:
    LDX     #>CHAR_SELECT_TABLE
    LDY     #<CHAR_SELECT_TABLE
    JMP     INPUT_LOOP

CHAR_SELECT_INIT:
    SUBROUTINE CHAR_SELECT_INIT
    JSR     FIND_FIRST_PC      ; find first player character
    BCC     CHAR_SELECT_HOME   ; carry clear -> found, enter init path
    JSR     SET_CURSOR_ROW21   ; no PCs: position cursor
    LDA     #MSG_SAVED_ME               ; message $35: "YOU SAVED ME..."
    JSR     DISPLAY_MESSAGE
    JMP     MOVE_LOOP          ; back to main loop

CHAR_SELECT_NEXT:
    JSR     $6071              ; patch menu record
    JSR     FIND_NEXT_PC_WRAP  ; advance to next PC
    JMP     ENTER_CHAR_SELECT

CHAR_SELECT_PREV:
    JSR     $6071              ; patch menu record
    JSR     FIND_PREV_PC       ; retreat to previous PC
    JMP     ENTER_CHAR_SELECT

; "TO THIS ROOM" handler: set ACTIVE_CHAR=1, disable rec4, -> .patch
CHAR_SELECT_HERE:
    LDA     #$01
    STA     ACTIVE_CHAR
    LDX     #$00
    BEQ     .patch             ; always taken

; "TO ALI BABA'S HOME" handler AND .found target from CHAR_SELECT_INIT.
; If CURRENT_PLAYER==9 -> CHAR_SELECT_HERE (enable rec5, disable rec4).
; Otherwise store CURRENT_PLAYER in ACTIVE_CHAR, disable rec5, enable rec4.
CHAR_SELECT_HOME:
    LDA     CURRENT_PLAYER
    CMP     #$09
    BEQ     CHAR_SELECT_HERE
    STA     ACTIVE_CHAR
    LDA     #$00               ; disable rec5
    LDX     #$01               ; enable rec4

.patch:
    STA     CHAR_SELECT_TABLE+54 ; rec5 byte 0 (enable/disable)
    STX     CHAR_SELECT_TABLE+44 ; rec4 byte 0 (enable/disable)
    LDY     #$02
    STY     CHAR_SELECT_TABLE+1  ; max_range = 2
    JMP     ENTER_CHAR_SELECT
@ %def ENTER_CHAR_SELECT CHAR_SELECT_INIT CHAR_SELECT_NEXT CHAR_SELECT_PREV CHAR_SELECT_HERE CHAR_SELECT_HOME

