small offset (e.g.\ [[STEP_PRNG]] was at [[$764A]] instead of
[[$78A8]]).  The first five bytes are garbled---an [[ORA $CE12]]
into expansion-ROM space followed by two undocumented NMOS~6502
[[$5A]] NOPs---suggesting the entry point was partially overwritten.

The only live byte is the [[RTS]] at [[$1FFE]], which serves as a
no-op stub for external callers at [[$4A1F]] and [[$4BE4]].

<<orphaned encounter handler>>=
